OL,5,CIF ASKED FOR A DANCE...       Q(.,.#   
OL,7, Bears who dance for their keeper's     
OL,8, living areCtrained as cubs,Gpoints out 
OL,9, Jonathan Owen of the World Society for 
OL,10, the Protection of Animals.             
OL,12, "TheirCmothers are killedGand they are 
OL,13, taken away from their natural habitat  
OL,14, in the wild. As you can imagine it's   
OL,15, extremely traumatic," he says,         
OL,17, "They are then trained to dance through
OL,18, the use ofCburning hot coalGon their   
OL,19, feet and music association."           
