OL,5,CIF ASKED FOR A DANCE...       Q(.,.#   
OL,7, There areClaws against bear dancingGin 
OL,8, many countries but the attraction      
OL,9, lingers because tourists support it.   
OL,11, So claims Jonathan Owen of the World   
OL,12, Society for the Protection of Animals, 
OL,13, who adds: "As a traveller,Cthe fate of 
OL,14,Cdancing bears lies in your hands.      
OL,16, "Don't support it and don't try to     
OL,17, intervene, it could be dangerous.      
OL,18, Instead report sightings of dancing    
OL,19, bears to us by callingC0171 793 0540." 
